detailed_goals: Initiate data collection from EHR for influenza cases from the last three years using standardized formats.
Collaborate with Clinical Lead and Medical Records Specialists to ensure data relevance and collection methodology aligns with operational needs.
Start preliminary data cleaning processes to ensure data quality and adherence to compiled data integrity guidelines.
Collaborate with Data Analysts to validate the accuracy of the collected data and ensure it meets the needed standards for clinical relevance.
Establish feedback mechanisms to assess the effectiveness of EHR data features and suggest modifications based on clinical insights.
Implement QA testing processes on the EHR data collection for influenza cases based on established protocols.
Document QA findings and work with Data Analysts to address any issues or discrepancies found during testing.
Attend training sessions on the EHR system's features for documenting influenza cases to reduce errors.
Provide feedback from clinical interactions to improve data collection processes.
Coordinate the ongoing training and onboarding activities across departments.
